name: Warung Mina Padangsambian
address: Jl. Gn. Tangkuban Perahu No.78x, Padangsambian Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
A nice place with good food like the other Warung Minas (there are more than one)

The menu, the quality, the price are the same with the other branches. Delicious, quick service, friendly staff and lovely antmosphere.

Plenty of parking and has a children playing ground.
review 2: the food is really good, clean place, many type of menus, really good restaurant
review 3: A restaurant that serves delicious food located in northern Padangsambian, Denpasar, Bali.  This restaurant is about 14 km from the airport and only takes about 22 minutes to get there.  Accessibility is very easy to reach because it is located on the side of the road which is wide enough for two cars at once.  Here there are various facilities available such as toilets, large parking areas, stages, and meeting rooms.  You can do various activities here such as having lunch, dinner, taking pictures, making videos.  For those of you who want to organize events such as meetings, competitions, birthday parties, social gatherings and other events, you can do it here.  For those of you who bring children, don't worry, because here there is also a playground or playground for children.  There are many things that you will see here, such as traditional restaurant buildings, large fish ponds, beautiful garden views, and other interesting things.  This restaurant is open from 10 am to 10 pm.  There is no entrance fee, but you are must to buy food and drinks here, because here they sell various types of food, ranging from processed fresh water fish to seafood dishes.  What is the best seller here that you must buy is real carp.  The price offered is not too expensive.  Come on, invite your family and loved ones to visit Warung Mina Padangsambian.
review 4: Lovely outdoor seating at the back. It is a huge restaurant (Joglo) with massive parking space in front. The food choices are varied and quite delicious. Staff are great. You can bring your own DJ apparently for your own party here.
review 5: Warung Mina is famous for good food, affordable, in a beautiful location. Just in the middle of busy area, this warung develops in a super quiet location. The pity is that the location, probably after COVID, is still not 100% available, and the general impression is it's partially abandoned. The staff is super caring.

name: Kost Turi House
address: Gg. Buana Turi, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
You can rent a room with monthly rates or can ask the owner if they provide daily rent.

Nice room and it's supported with mini kitchen, water heater, small fridge, bed and tv. It's also located in area that provides local food and supplies.

Bonus: they do have huge rooftop which you can stargaze during Nyepi and enjoy sunset üåÖ
review 2: very completed kost (studio apartment) with affordable price you got furnished space. They also have daiky rent start from 50k

review 1:

The cashier need to smile more and say sorry when she forget to bring spoon and fork to any customer.

The food was good, price is ok. No wonder that the place with such a pretty good menu and good place can also be mostly empty all the time.
review 2: One of cheap resto with great foods! I love their ricebowl and ayam kremes so much. The vibe and interior it‚Äôs cute, even tho the rooftop kinda messy but i still love this place! The staff was very nice and kind but sometimes their speed of wifi is a bit slow. But it‚Äôs still a nice place to hang out with your friends! ü§©üëç

was tasted their ayam geprek, it was good, spiced properly, the sambal was awesome!
friendly staff, speedy in  serving, good parking space
review 4: I order take away. Efficient communication, nice food, clear menu, affordable price.
review 5: Comfortable restaurant to dine in, affordable food, taste good & clean. I reccomend their grilled chicken (ayam bakar) 18k or their ayam kremes.

address: 85QJ+VMQ, Jl. Padang Indah, Padangsambian Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
well i've known this food perhaps like 3 yrs ago and the taste never failed me whether you order online via Gojek or eat directly at the place.
but you need to bring cash if you want to eat directly there.
for me its better to takeaway as the place is small and no parking lot.
i bought the Lontong Sayur & Nasi Uduk already include with crackers , i also bought 2 ice tea and that all cost me for only IDR 45,000.
review 2: Favorite nasi uduk in Bali‚ù§Ô∏è my meal only cost me 15k

name: Mie Ayam Bakso Solo Wonogiri
address: Jl. Gn. Tangkuban Perahu, Padangsambian Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: You can enjoy orthodox taste of Bakso and Noodle in Bali. It's filled with local people of every generation every time. It's easy for order even if you don't know their language so that they will give you the price cards when the dish delivered. Don't forget to pay for the parking fee when you leave with your motorbike.
review 2:
Taste good, price affordable and fast service.

Dine in Ok for 2-3 people. Not suit for big group.
review 3: Great food if you looking for chicken noodle, they have their signature taste and it's can be considered as cheap food with expensive taste.
review 4: Mie Ayam is the best option here!!! Personally,  I don't like their meatball. Reasonable price, quite busy on dinner time!!! Car parking bit hard and recomend go by a motorcycle.
review 5: Mie ayam is the best menu here! I didn't really like the meatballs, but the chicken noodle is very delicious! The place is literalky for eating (there is no photo spot and didn't match to chitchat or just chillin). You can take away tho!

name: Paon Jonsonn
address: Padangsambian Klod, Denpasar Barat, Denpasar City, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: Wish more people know this place, best local pork ribs ever. The ribs are super tender and easily separated from its bone, price was affordable and the taste also amazing, no wonder many people loves it. Not to mention they have good ayam bakar too, gonna try it next time
review 2: Best ribs I have eaten in my life! Meat is falling from the bone and the flavour is amazing. Greetings from the Netherlands.
review 3: Very delicious tender spare ribs and a very friendly host. Would recommend to anyone!
review 4: I highly recommend this place. The dishes are just too good for my tummy and price is also reasonable. If you are a pork fan boy, come to this restaurant, and you won't regret it :)

review 2: Good Babi guling, although the skin is a bit thick but still crispy. The Lawar & soup is also good.
review 3: Affordable. Great takeaway packaging ! For white people maybey a little bit too spicey doh

Some tasty pork dishes with an indo flavour at a good price.

Just avoid the bathroom...
review 5: Typical balinese warung, nice pork, must try to eat

address: 85RP+XCP, Padangsambian, Denpasar Barat, Denpasar City, Bali 80118, Indonesia
review 1: Good price, very delicious food. I love it here. This place has been here for a long time. Just on the side of the street. The place is a bit rough and dusty. And you need to tell them to clean your table or you will have a lot of dust. Apart from that  price is reasonable and it tastes good
review 3: My all time favourite seafood restaurant. Try their sapo tahu, ikan goreng mentega, nasi goreng ikan asin, and kepiting saos padang. So far, they never failed me. Well, actually the taste not really that delicious (don't set your very high expectations), but the money you'll spent compared with the taste of the food is totally worth it!
review 4: Great selection chinese food and taste good
review 5: Overall food was ok..not expensive..but compare wth similar warung/resto..they're food was delicious
